  "prompt": "I'm new to Quora. What does it mean when someone says they are following me?",
  "response": "Welcome to Quora! When someone says they are following you on Quora, it means they\u2019ve chosen to keep track of your activity on the platform. Here\u2019s what it typically entails:\n\n1. **Your Content in Their Feed**: When you post questions, answers, or share content, it may appear in their Quora feed. This helps them stay updated on what you\u2019re contributing.\n\n2. **No Obligation**: Following you doesn\u2019t necessarily mean they know you personally; they might just find your content interesting or valuable.\n\n3. **Notification Settings**: They can choose how often they\u2019re notified about your activity, depending on their Quora notification preferences.\n\n4. **One-Way Connection**: Following someone is not mutual. If they follow you, you don\u2019t automatically follow them back unless you choose to do so.\n\nIf someone follows you, it\u2019s often a sign that they appreciate your contributions or want to engage with your content. It\u2019s a positive way to build connections and share knowledge on the platform!",
